To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, I need to divide the Gross Profit by the Total Revenue, then express it as a percentage.

Looking at the income statement:
- Gross Profit = $2,861,769.51
- Total Revenue = $4,879,769.51

Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = ($2,861,769.51 / $4,879,769.51) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 0.5864 × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 58.64%
